*Arch Linux* is my favourite Linux distribution (LD), especially when it comes to building packages. This is because the PKGBUILD format is very intuitive, simple and written in my favourite programming language &mdash; Shell. The objective of writing a PKGBUILD is to build the package in the `${srcdir}` directory (usually in the `src` subfolder of the directory the PKGBUILD is in)
